# Secondhand Items API Documentation

## Base Path

```
/api
```

---

## 1. Create a New Secondhand Item

- **Endpoint:** `POST /api/secondhand`
- **Description:** Create a new secondhand item.
- **Request Body:**
  ```json
  {
    "sellerId": 123,
    "title": "iPhone 13 Pro",
    "description": "Almost new, no scratches, all accessories included",
    "price": "5999.00",
    "image": "https://example.com/images/iphone13pro.jpg",
    "status": "available" // available | sold | reserved
  }
  ```
- **Response:**
  - `201 Created`  
    Returns the created item object.
  - `400 Bad Request`  
    Invalid input.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 2. Get All Secondhand Items

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/secondhand`
- **Description:** Retrieve a list of all secondhand items.
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns an array of item objects.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 3. Get Secondhand Item by ID

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/secondhand/{id}`
- **Description:** Retrieve details of a specific secondhand item by its ID.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Item ID
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns the item object.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 4. Update a Secondhand Item

- **Endpoint:** `PUT /api/secondhand/{id}`
- **Description:** Update an existing secondhand item.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Item ID
- **Request Body:** (any of the following fields)
  ```json
  {
    "sellerId": 123,
    "title": "Updated Title",
    "description": "Updated description",
    "price": "5999.00",
    "image": "https://example.com/images/updated.jpg",
    "status": "sold" // available | sold | reserved
  }
  ```
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns the updated item object.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 5. Delete a Secondhand Item

- **Endpoint:** `DELETE /api/secondhand/{id}`
- **Description:** Delete a secondhand item by its ID.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Item ID
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns a success message.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 6. Review a Secondhand Item (Approve/Reject)

- **Endpoint:** `PUT /api/secondhand/{id}/review`
- **Description:** Review a secondhand item (approve or reject).
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `id` (integer, required): Item ID
- **Request Body:**
  ```json
  {
    "reviewerId": 456,
    "approved": true,
    "reason": "Item information is complete and meets requirements"
  }
  ```
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns the reviewed item object.
  - `404 Not Found`
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

---

## 7. Get User's Secondhand Items

- **Endpoint:** `GET /api/users/{userId}/secondhand`
- **Description:** Get all secondhand items posted by a specific user.
- **Path Parameter:**
  - `userId` (integer, required): User ID
- **Response:**
  - `200 OK`  
    Returns an array of item objects.
  - `500 Internal Server Error`

